article.headline: Oral Roberts 91, Panhandle State 41
article.story: TULSA, Okla. (AP) -- Marchello Vealy scored 19 points and grabbed eight rebounds to help lead Oral Roberts to a 91-41 victory over Panhandle State on Saturday. Caleb Green added 17 points and six rebounds and the Golden Eagles (3-1) got 16 points, four rebounds and three assists from Ken Tutt. Oral Roberts extended its 36-22 halftime lead, outscoring the Aggies 55-19 in the second half, when Panhandle State hit just 5-of-22 (22.7 percent) shots. The Golden Eagles shot 46.4 percent (32-of-69) from the field for the game, including 21-of-26 free throws. Oral Roberts outrebounded the Aggies 47-23. LaChawn Anderson paced Panhandle State (1-3) with 14 points and five rebounds. Fred Durr added 11 points for the Aggies, who shot just 28 percent from the field for the game and committed 22 turnovers.
